{"id":"428835640537739_497536510334318","type":"status","created_time":"2013-07-03T22:37:26+0000","message":"Judge Adly Mansour was named the new head of Egypt\u2019s High Constitutional Court (HCC) on Sunday. Mansour, formerly the court's vice-president, succeeds Judge Maher El-Beheiry whose term ended on 30 June.\n\nAccording to HCC law 48, which was amended in 2011, \u201cThe head of the court must be appointed by the president, who chooses from among the court's three oldest vice-presidents. His decision must be approved by the court\u2019s general assembly.\u201d"}